      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERFECT BANDIT (7) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when second and beaten a neck at this track over 350m in 19.77. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Likely to feature again. CYCLADES (8) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at this track, but was among the placings at this track three back. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Has the ability and can find best this time. TAW MYSTIQUE (4) could manage only third last time but ran useful time (20.63) at Nowra over 365m when beaten 3.5 lengths in a Grade 5. This is tougher but looks a leading chance again. WINTER KEY (1) is new here but cannot be left out.",
